Russia requested the call, according to The New York Times. Per the White House, Putin and Biden spoke for about 50 minutes. The leaders last call that was made known to the public was on December 7, when Russia said it would send ideas on the crisis to Washington "within a week," Reuters reported. - Ukraine has been a point of contention for the two countries since the annexation of Crimea in 2014, Al Jazeera reports
